<p><a href="index.html?p=581#_ednref7" name="_edn7">[7]</a> Only one scene that I remember had the irreverent Moore touch—when Gibbs and Zehner (and an unseen photographer) are threatened for having trespassed on property of a company they are trying to expose. They express mock innocence but gradually make their way off the property.</p>
